# Build context for both docker/Dockerfile.api and docker/Dockerfile.dashboard
# is the repository root (docker-compose.yml sets `context: .`) — one shared
# .dockerignore covers both; there is nothing image-specific to say here
# (each Dockerfile's own COPY lines already pick only what that image needs
# from whatever reaches the daemon).
#
# None of this is a training-vs-serving distinction (that's what the two
# COPY lists in the Dockerfiles do) — this file exists purely to keep the
# build context small and the images free of local/secret/dev-only state
# that should never end up in an image layer.

# --- Training-side data and model artifacts (gitignored; never needed to
# serve). NEVER add /artifacts/ here — that's the
# committed runtime tree both Dockerfiles explicitly COPY in.
/data/
/models/
mlruns/
mlflow.db
/ingest_report/
/reports/

# --- VCS / editor / OS
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# --- Environment / secrets — never bake a real .env into an image
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- Python build & cache
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
build/
dist/
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
coverage.xml
htmlcov/
.ruff_cache/

# --- Local dev-launcher logs (scripts/dev.py)
/logs/

# --- Jupyter
.ipynb_checkpoints/
notebooks/

# --- Internal engineering notes (machine-local)
.ai/
.claude/
.agents/
/context/

# --- Not needed inside either image (neither Dockerfile COPYs these —
# excluded here only to keep the context sent to the daemon small)
tests/
docs/
.github/
*.md
